   3.922850234786234*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"54de71b1-5a9f-4849-8451-\
c52cd4a51b3b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Filtration of the conjoint composite fully-contracted terms", \
"Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874644843789677*^9, 3.8746448545752873`*^9}, {
   3.883112065177337*^9, 3.883112118360941*^9}, {3.8831146011227875`*^9, 
   3.8831146201744213`*^9}, {3.883115184479356*^9, 3.8831151965813236`*^9}, {
   3.8884058729915524`*^9, 3.8884058731821747`*^9}, {3.892800153537215*^9, 
   3.8928001610648518`*^9}, {3.897041751372193*^9, 3.8970417738128204`*^9}, {
   3.8970432846114845`*^9, 3.897043286022911*^9}, 3.911883818478182*^9, {
   3.9140585836908464`*^9, 
   3.914058588389393*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0d801606-6177-4a37-aed0-\
f5661c47b318"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the conjoint composite fully-contracted terms. At third \
order, transpositions between single particles of both different vertices \
(external permutations) and the same vertex (internal permutations) are \
possible. Fully-contracted terms which are mapped one another by the \
permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"05531c1d-5edf-4c95-99f1-950aed384e68"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3facf28b-d7c7-4518-a385-4b2f69d1182b"],
 " interaction vertex. Simultaneously, diagrams which are mapped one another \
by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u, v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are also identified and summed, eventually canceling out the other ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"714033a1-12a4-426d-98bf-a91d6dc5fc32"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "tuvw"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d8892c59-6625-4430-b4cf-7b3d714df3d0"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two vertices. Conversely, \
for the one-body vertices no symmetry property applies, and permutations \
between one-body vertices are not available. As a result, 1,800 third-order \
conjoint composite fully-contracted terms of this kind are found."
