Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Filtration of the above-and-below-dressed disjoint exchange fully-contracted \
terms\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874644843789677*^9, 3.8746448545752873`*^9}, {
   3.883112065177337*^9, 3.883112118360941*^9}, {3.8831146011227875`*^9, 
   3.8831146201744213`*^9}, {3.883115184479356*^9, 3.8831151965813236`*^9}, {
   3.8884058729915524`*^9, 3.8884058731821747`*^9}, {3.892800153537215*^9, 
   3.8928001610648518`*^9}, {3.897041751372193*^9, 3.8970417738128204`*^9}, {
   3.8970432846114845`*^9, 3.897043286022911*^9}, 3.911883818478182*^9, {
   3.9140585836908464`*^9, 3.914058588389393*^9}, {3.9143026289257283`*^9, 
   3.9143026345631857`*^9}, {3.9143032525134974`*^9, 3.914303253172863*^9}, {
   3.9143032906729994`*^9, 3.9143032911764235`*^9}, {3.9143044455578475`*^9, 
   3.9143044537230844`*^9}, {3.9143051247453966`*^9, 
   3.9143051278635187`*^9}, {3.914312565124779*^9, 
   3.9143125676424713`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6ca35477-9b77-490f-92ae-\
5a51deb1f010"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the above-and-below-dressed disjoint exchange \
fully-contracted terms. At third order, transpositions between single \
particles of both different vertices (external permutations) and the same \
vertex (internal permutations) are possible. Fully-contracted terms which are \
mapped one another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"689a5708-1939-44be-b3a2-44bd4a11ef4f"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5b561ede-cdff-4666-a5d9-5ccaba56a260"],
 " interaction vertex. Simultaneously, diagrams which are mapped one another \
by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u, v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are also identified and summed, eventually canceling out the other ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"4fcb45a5-469e-458e-bcc1-c30ee6840f7d"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "tuvw"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d6525915-3bd9-49a6-ad22-0d73f46cbf35"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two vertices. Conversely, \
for the one-body vertices no symmetry property applies, and permutations \
between one-body vertices are not available. As a result, 328 third-order \
above-and-below-dressed disjoint exchange fully-contracted terms of this kind \
are found."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
   3.88368123630155*^9}, {3.8884066008391533`*^9, 3.8884066027299986`*^9}, {
   3.8897788646156874`*^9, 3.8897788665710464`*^9}, {3.8926969246265383`*^9, 
   3.8926970411577735`*^9}, {3.892698767515374*^9, 3.8926988019171734`*^9}, {
