c4dc159de23a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the antidiagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov \
fully-contracted terms. At third order, transpositions between single \
particles of both different vertices (external permutations) and the same \
vertex (internal permutations) are possible. Fully-contracted terms which are \
mapped one another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"c30008c2-d5fd-443a-a3d2-be30ffc58215"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d867c3ba-67b3-42af-82a8-316696ba07c2"],
 " interaction vertex. Simultaneously, diagrams which are mapped one another \
by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u, v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are also identified and summed, eventually canceling out the other ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"a940af46-2bf2-4dce-95a6-8ceac184df48"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "tuvw"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "459eb0b8-fdde-4973-a009-b44d3dbf0f90"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two vertices. Conversely, \
for the one-body vertices no symmetry property applies, and permutations \
between one-body vertices are not available. As a result, 340 third-order \
antidiagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov fully-contracted terms of this \
kind are found."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
   3.88368123630155*^9}, {3.8884066008391533`*^9, 3.8884066027299986`*^9}, {
   3.8897788646156874`*^9, 3.8897788665710464`*^9}, {3.8926969246265383`*^9, 
