   3.9143130931058297`*^9}, {3.9143140902869225`*^9, 
   3.9143140910707874`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"20f3a968-4048-4398-9f58-\
daec7fb03c52"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the diagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov fully-contracted \
terms. At third order, transpositions between single particles of both \
different vertices (external permutations) and the same vertex (internal \
permutations) are possible. Fully-contracted terms which are mapped one \
another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"f1aba805-933e-4652-a215-0d4f74940c5f"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d89e71c3-c934-4a53-9404-9a5cfe700a05"],
 " interaction vertex. Simultaneously, diagrams which are mapped one another \
by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u, v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are also identified and summed, eventually canceling out the other ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"3594e442-fbf8-4289-89c3-b4f950ae4114"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "tuvw"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fe579f35-1ceb-4af3-bac1-6d4611509d2d"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two vertices. Conversely, \
for the one-body vertices no symmetry property applies, and permutations \
between one-body vertices are not available. As a result, 340 third-order \
diagonally-dressed disjoint Bogoliubov fully-contracted terms of this kind \
are found."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
   3.88368123630155*^9}, {3.8884066008391533`*^9, 3.8884066027299986`*^9}, {
   3.8897788646156874`*^9, 3.8897788665710464`*^9}, {3.8926969246265383`*^9, 
   3.8926970411577735`*^9}, {3.892698767515374*^9, 3.8926988019171734`*^9}, {
   3.892698944167777*^9, 3.89269895025534*^9}, 3.897980551930337*^9, {
   3.9118989337632127`*^9, 3.9118991105611753`*^9}, {3.911899164309193*^9, 
   3.911899190598539*^9}, {3.9119021521938486`*^9, 3.9119021639529204`*^9}, {
   3.91190327426869*^9, 3.9119033058295913`*^9}, {3.911906807421135*^9, 
   3.9119068216883116`*^9}, {3.9119699970418005`*^9, 
   3.9119699984191523`*^9}, {3.914058593986375*^9, 3.9140586012399297`*^9}, {
   3.914058989288723*^9, 3.9140590822310486`*^9}, {3.9143026405637946`*^9, 
