Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the disconnected fully-contracted terms. At third order, \
transpositions between single particles of both different vertices (external \
permutations) and the same vertex (internal permutations) are possible. \
Fully-contracted terms which are mapped one another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"5db57cc4-a0e6-4825-9c71-ed1604250b30"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "55a66353-b31d-4333-8a40-5657262a8976"],
 " interaction vertex. Simultaneously, diagrams which are mapped one another \
by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u, v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are also identified and summed, eventually canceling out the other ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"4ba83091-be52-424c-8c8e-eec4b396623b"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "tuvw"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7d3202d3-80d3-424a-827a-ea944a84dc82"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two vertices. Conversely, \
for the one-body vertices no symmetry property applies, and permutations \
between one-body vertices are not available. As a result, 1,401 third-order \
disconnected fully-contracted terms of this kind are found."
}], "Text",
